 leaders thereafter, arriving at an original and comprehensive view of the close interrelations between the political and spiritual spheres of the time.   The author considers the powerful religious dimension of French royal power even in the seventeenth century, the shift from reluctant toleration of a Protestant minority to increasing aversion, conflicts over the independence of the Catholic church and the power of the pope over secular rulers, and a wealth of other interconnected topics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianity and politicszFrancexHistoryy17th century. 0aChurch and statezFrancexHistoryy17th century. 0aProtestantismzFrancexHistoryy17th century. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030020769940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021046040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210460423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300210460/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY